        <updateDate>2022-01-26T19:15:40Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p>This bill requires the Department of the Treasury to instruct the U.S. executive directors at certain multilateral development banks, such as the Asian Development Bank, to oppose providing a loan, financial assistance, or technical assistance to China. The executive directors must also advocate and vote to end lending and assistance to a country that has exceeded certain income thresholds.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>A bill to oppose the provision of assistance to the People's Republic of China by the multilateral development banks.</title>
